i'm trying to do this:

// typescript
get getWidth(): number {
    // this._el is an inject(ElementRef);
    const width = +this._el.nativeElement.querySelector(
      '[id="fs-img-container"]'
    ).clientWidth;

    return (80 / 100) * width - 1;
}
get getHeight(): number {
    const height = +this._el.nativeElement.querySelector(
      '[id="fs-img-container"]'
    ).clientHeight;

    return (80 / 100) * height - 1;
}

// html
<img
  ngSrc="assets/hero-illustration.svg"
  [width]="getWidth"
  [height]="getHeight"
/>

This works perfectly and the expected result is obtained, however in the console it shows the following error:
ERROR RuntimeError: NG02952: The NgOptimizedImage directive (activated on an <img> element with the `ngSrc="assets/hero-illustration.svg"`) has detected that `height` has an invalid value. To fix this, provide `height` as a number greater than 0.
